WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.130 --> 00:00:01.330
<i>Previously on "The Rookie"...</i>

2
00:00:01.360 --> 00:00:02.240
What's all this?

3
00:00:02.270 --> 00:00:04.460
I'm studying for the
detective's exam.

4
00:00:04.850 --> 00:00:05.820
Monica.

5
00:00:05.850 --> 00:00:07.740
<i>She's smart. fairly ruthless.</i>

6
00:00:07.770 --> 00:00:09.620
and God forbid you leave
the toilet seat up.

7
00:00:09.640 --> 00:00:11.070
Celina. look out!

8
00:00:11.090 --> 00:00:12.810
<i>It seems obvious that
they were targeted.</i>

9
00:00:12.830 --> 00:00:14.260
Bailey!

10
00:00:14.290 --> 00:00:15.120
Leah!

11
00:00:15.150 --> 00:00:17.040
Hi. Oh.

12
00:00:17.070 --> 00:00:19.090
Angela had the
baby. It's a girl.

13
00:00:19.110 --> 00:00:21.380
- Hey.
- Hey.

14
00:00:23.160 --> 00:00:24.340
What's happening?

15
00:00:24.370 --> 00:00:26.090
The list of possible
masterminds.

16
00:00:26.120 --> 00:00:27.180
you were at the bottom.

17
00:00:27.200 --> 00:00:29.430
Weaponizing Luke
Moran against the LAPD

18
00:00:29.450 --> 00:00:32.310
has driven every cop in the
city away from our target.

19
00:00:32.330 --> 00:00:34.890
<i>By the time they realize
the damage we've done.</i>

20
00:00:34.920 --> 00:00:36.380
we'll be long gone.

21
00:00:50.310 --> 00:00:51.650
Shots fired.

22
00:00:51.670 --> 00:00:53.450
I am pinned down out
front. I need help.

23
00:01:01.780 --> 00:01:03.170
Aaron's bleeding internally.

24
00:01:03.200 --> 00:01:05.050
A surgeon must have
missed a bullet fragment.

25
00:01:05.070 --> 00:01:06.300
They're rushing
him into surgery.

26
00:01:06.320 --> 00:01:07.300
Is he gonna be all right?

27
00:01:07.320 --> 00:01:08.430
<i>I-I don't know.</i>

28
00:01:08.450 --> 00:01:09.430
What do I do?

29
00:01:09.450 --> 00:01:10.850
Nothing you can do.

30
00:01:10.870 --> 00:01:12.470
Just be there to watch over him.

31
00:01:12.500 --> 00:01:13.970
Do you guys need help? Is
there anything I can do to...

32
00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:16.290
Negative. You still haven't
been cleared medically.

33
00:01:17.170 --> 00:01:18.710
Celina.

34
00:01:20.460 --> 00:01:21.940
We heard Aaron's
back in surgery.

35
00:01:21.960 --> 00:01:23.400
Yeah. they just rushed him in.

36
00:01:23.420 --> 00:01:25.190
I. uh... I'm... I'm
on with Sergeant Grey.

37
00:01:25.220 --> 00:01:26.700
Wait. you guys are
checking out already?

38
00:01:26.720 --> 00:01:28.990
- You just had the baby.
- It's too noisy here.

39
00:01:29.010 --> 00:01:30.910
We got the pediatrician
to sign off.

40
00:01:30.930 --> 00:01:32.260
- We're going home.
- Unless Grey needs

41
00:01:32.280 --> 00:01:33.640
<i>- something from us.</i>
- Negative.

42
00:01:33.670 --> 00:01:36.120
Just please stick with
your police escort.

43
00:01:36.150 --> 00:01:38.750
I thought we caught
the mastermind. but

44
00:01:38.770 --> 00:01:41.000
now I'm not too sure.

45
00:01:41.030 --> 00:01:43.630
All right. explain it to
me like I'm a toddler.

46
00:01:43.650 --> 00:01:46.630
This assault was well
funded and well executed.

47
00:01:46.660 --> 00:01:48.840
But Lucas Moran
had $12 in the bank

48
00:01:48.870 --> 00:01:50.800
and a well-documented
history of being a loner.

49
00:01:50.830 --> 00:01:52.390
We're not buying he
had the resources

50
00:01:52.410 --> 00:01:54.310
- to pull off the attack.
- Or the contacts.

51
00:01:54.330 --> 00:01:57.230
Maybe he met someone in
prison who helped him.

52
00:01:57.250 --> 00:01:59.560
Most likely. but who's
gonna spend a fortune

53
00:01:59.590 --> 00:02:01.520
to kick a hornet's nest?

54
00:02:01.550 --> 00:02:04.070
Who volunteers to piss
off the entire LAPD?

55
00:02:04.090 --> 00:02:05.480
Somebody with their own agenda.

56
00:02:05.510 --> 00:02:07.490
Yeah. who wanted to focus
our attention on a patsy.

57
00:02:07.510 --> 00:02:09.570
Divert all of our resources
to this neighborhood

58
00:02:09.600 --> 00:02:10.820
so they can pull
off a new crime.

59
00:02:10.850 --> 00:02:11.960
A new crime like what?

60
00:02:11.990 --> 00:02:13.460
No clue. But I'd bet my life

61
00:02:13.490 --> 00:02:14.510
it's happening right now.

62
00:02:17.560 --> 00:02:19.770
60 seconds ahead of schedule.
Let's keep it tight.

63
00:02:26.110 --> 00:02:28.630
All right. we've been
through this a dozen times.

64
00:02:28.660 --> 00:02:30.470
Cyesha and her crew
meet the inside man

65
00:02:30.490 --> 00:02:31.930
and gain control of
the security room

66
00:02:31.950 --> 00:02:33.220
while we take the lobby.

67
00:02:33.240 --> 00:02:35.310
Then 20 minutes to
load the armored car

68
00:02:35.330 --> 00:02:36.810
while Kim does her thing.

69
00:02:36.830 --> 00:02:38.770
You're really not gonna
tell us what Kim's thing is?

70
00:02:38.790 --> 00:02:41.390
Correct. Just focus on
your individual jobs.

71
00:02:41.420 --> 00:02:44.190
and we will be made of
money by this evening.

72
00:02:44.210 --> 00:02:46.190
All right. synchronize.

73
00:02:46.220 --> 00:02:48.030
Three. two. one.

74
00:02:48.050 --> 00:02:49.240
Mark.

75
00:02:49.260 --> 00:02:50.240
Let's go.

76
00:03:05.940 --> 00:03:07.420
Good afternoon. gentlemen.

77
00:03:07.440 --> 00:03:08.800
Any problems?

78
00:03:08.820 --> 00:03:10.170
No. they're all in
the security cage

79
00:03:10.200 --> 00:03:11.440
for change of shift.

80
00:03:12.620 --> 00:03:14.930
I am Glen Mercer. U.S.
Treasury Department.

81
00:03:14.950 --> 00:03:17.220
West Coast Chief
Security Officer.

82
00:03:17.250 --> 00:03:20.310
And I'm here for an unscheduled
security inspection.

83
00:03:23.590 --> 00:03:25.770
<i>Yeah!</i>

84
00:03:30.800 --> 00:03:32.550
Grab the guns. kill the feeds.

85
00:03:33.600 --> 00:03:34.720
Hey!

86
00:03:35.970 --> 00:03:37.410
- What the...
- Stop 'em!

87
00:03:40.060 --> 00:03:41.150
What do I do?

88
00:03:44.270 --> 00:03:45.920
Nothing. Your part's over.

89
00:03:51.660 --> 00:03:52.840
Phase One complete.

90
00:03:52.870 --> 00:03:54.470
Copy that. Moving
on to Phase Two.

91
00:03:54.490 --> 00:03:55.870
What?

92
00:03:58.910 --> 00:04:00.600
All right.

93
00:04:03.420 --> 00:04:05.230
<i>Negative. 7-Metro-100.</i>

94
00:04:05.250 --> 00:04:06.810
<i>There have been no
high-priority calls</i>

95
00:04:06.840 --> 00:04:08.400
<i>in the last two
hours beside yours.</i>

96
00:04:08.420 --> 00:04:09.820
All right. dispatch.
switch gears.

97
00:04:09.840 --> 00:04:11.110
I want any anomalies.

98
00:04:11.130 --> 00:04:12.530
no matter how small
or seemingly random

99
00:04:12.550 --> 00:04:14.610
<i>false alarm. noise
complaint that seems odd.</i>

100
00:04:14.640 --> 00:04:18.030
Or totally crazy... UFO
sightings. mole people.

101
00:04:18.060 --> 00:04:19.660
<i>Aside from your earlier action.</i>

102
00:04:19.680 --> 00:04:21.080
<i>it's a normal day in LA.</i>

103
00:04:21.100 --> 00:04:23.200
<i>We average a dozen
bizarre calls an hour.</i>

104
00:04:23.230 --> 00:04:25.370
<i>But none have been from
high-value targets.</i>

105
00:04:25.400 --> 00:04:27.290
Ah. come on. there's
got to be something.

106
00:04:27.320 --> 00:04:29.010
<i>Hold on. This is
a little unusual.</i>

107
00:04:29.030 --> 00:04:31.420
<i>The Federal Reserve Bank
has an hourly check-in call</i>

108
00:04:31.450 --> 00:04:33.210
<i>which is late.</i>

109
00:04:33.240 --> 00:04:34.840
- How late?
<i>- 17 seconds.</i>

110
00:04:34.870 --> 00:04:36.260
That's barely a blip.

111
00:04:36.280 --> 00:04:37.770
But it's all we've got to go on.

112
00:04:37.800 --> 00:04:40.180
- How often are they late?
<i>- Rarely. but it happens.</i>

113
00:04:40.200 --> 00:04:41.970
Federal Reserve is definitely
a high-value target.

114
00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:43.350
All right. I'm a few
blocks from there.

115
00:04:43.370 --> 00:04:45.050
I'll swing by.
I'll check it out.

116
00:04:49.250 --> 00:04:50.630
We might have a problem.

117
00:04:52.670 --> 00:04:54.280
Cop's outside.

118
00:05:12.610 --> 00:05:14.260
7-Adam-15 on site.

119
00:05:14.280 --> 00:05:15.660
Lobby's empty.

120
00:05:21.040 --> 00:05:22.720
Check that. There's
blood inside.

121
00:05:22.750 --> 00:05:23.890
They're robbing the
Federal Reserve.

122
00:05:23.910 --> 00:05:25.100
Send backup. airship.

123
00:05:25.120 --> 00:05:27.050
and an ambulance in
case of casualties.

124
00:05:46.650 --> 00:05:47.910
- Time's up.
- How the hell

125
00:05:47.940 --> 00:05:49.620
did the cops get
onto us so fast?

126
00:05:49.650 --> 00:05:51.380
I don't know. But we got to go.

127
00:06:02.200 --> 00:06:03.180
Almost there.

128
00:06:03.200 --> 00:06:05.010
- Not good enough.
- Tough.

129
00:06:05.040 --> 00:06:06.600
You need to buy me
another five minutes

130
00:06:06.620 --> 00:06:08.810
to get through
this last firewall.

131
00:06:11.170 --> 00:06:13.770
Cyesha. we need to
pivot to Plan B.

132
00:06:13.800 --> 00:06:15.400
Sacrifice the lambs.

133
00:06:15.420 --> 00:06:16.690
Copy.

134
00:06:17.180 --> 00:06:18.990
Let's go.

135
00:06:19.410 --> 00:06:21.170
- Leave it!
- Let's go.

136
00:07:10.440 --> 00:07:11.910
Shots fired.

137
00:07:11.940 --> 00:07:14.080
I am pinned down out
front. I need help.

138
00:07:19.710 --> 00:07:21.320
Duck!

139
00:07:37.170 --> 00:07:38.360
Finished.

140
00:07:38.380 --> 00:07:39.900
And I injected a
virus that'll make it

141
00:07:39.930 --> 00:07:42.030
impossible to figure
out what we did.

142
00:07:42.050 --> 00:07:44.200
Suspect's down.

143
00:07:46.850 --> 00:07:48.660
He's not conscious.
Not breathing.

144
00:07:48.680 --> 00:07:50.750
Appears the shot came from
the third-floor window.

145
00:07:50.770 --> 00:07:52.460
They sniped their own guy.

146
00:07:52.480 --> 00:07:53.750
Why would they do that?

147
00:07:53.780 --> 00:07:55.500
They must have a
secondary escape route.

148
00:07:55.520 --> 00:07:57.960
Didn't want to leave anyone
behind to flip on them.

149
00:07:57.980 --> 00:07:59.590
The tunnels.

150
00:07:59.610 --> 00:08:01.420
Let's get units rolling
to the egress points.

151
00:08:01.450 --> 00:08:02.760
We don't have anybody close by.

152
00:08:02.780 --> 00:08:04.720
Harper. Nolan. you're with me.

153
00:08:17.840 --> 00:08:19.440
Shots fired. basement hallway.

154
00:08:19.460 --> 00:08:20.510
Four suspects.

155
00:08:22.510 --> 00:08:23.550
Ah!

156
00:08:25.300 --> 00:08:26.760
Come on. Go. go. go. go!

157
00:08:57.960 --> 00:08:59.940
- Are you nervous?
- Nope.

158
00:08:59.960 --> 00:09:01.770
Last shift before the wedding.

159
00:09:01.800 --> 00:09:03.650
- Yep.
- But you're still not nervous?

160
00:09:03.680 --> 00:09:05.900
Nope. What about you?

161
00:09:05.930 --> 00:09:07.410
- What about me?
- Are you nervous

162
00:09:07.430 --> 00:09:08.700
that Detective Harper
will be taking over

163
00:09:08.720 --> 00:09:10.120
your training in my absence?

164
00:09:10.140 --> 00:09:12.830
Oh. I... she...

165
00:09:12.850 --> 00:09:14.330
- When did that happen?
- Last night.

166
00:09:14.350 --> 00:09:15.410
Unless you'd prefer
Sergeant Bradford.

167
00:09:15.440 --> 00:09:16.660
No. no.

168
00:09:16.690 --> 00:09:18.620
Well... no. No. no.

169
00:09:18.650 --> 00:09:19.960
What about Smitty?

170
00:09:19.980 --> 00:09:21.400
I'm kidding.

171
00:09:21.420 --> 00:09:23.190
No. Detective Harper.
she's... she's great.

172
00:09:23.220 --> 00:09:26.780
I mean. I'm sure I will
learn so much from her.

173
00:09:27.030 --> 00:09:28.840
Not that you haven't
already taught me

174
00:09:28.870 --> 00:09:31.300
everything I need to know.

175
00:09:31.330 --> 00:09:32.600
Well. not that I still
don't have a lot of holes

176
00:09:32.620 --> 00:09:33.810
in my training

177
00:09:33.830 --> 00:09:35.810
okay. not because
you're a bad TO.

178
00:09:35.830 --> 00:09:37.520
It's...

179
00:09:37.540 --> 00:09:40.440
Oh. thank God.

180
00:09:40.460 --> 00:09:42.820
- What's the problem?
- My husband's missing.

181
00:09:42.850 --> 00:09:45.670
He... he went out last night.
and I haven't heard from him...

182
00:09:54.270 --> 00:09:56.370
Oh. no.

183
00:10:01.650 --> 00:10:04.130
Officers.

184
00:10:04.150 --> 00:10:05.420
Found him.

185
00:10:07.200 --> 00:10:09.220
This way.

186
00:10:09.240 --> 00:10:12.050
Any. um. advice to help optimize

187
00:10:12.080 --> 00:10:13.760
my experience with
Detective Harper?

188
00:10:13.790 --> 00:10:15.430
- No.
- Why not?

189
00:10:15.460 --> 00:10:18.270
Because so much of what we do
is dealing with the unknown.

190
00:10:18.290 --> 00:10:20.690
I don't do you any service
by giving you cheat codes.

191
00:10:20.710 --> 00:10:21.900
Cheat codes? For what?

192
00:10:21.920 --> 00:10:23.060
- No. nothing.
- Training with you.

193
00:10:23.090 --> 00:10:25.070
Oh. there are no
cheat codes for me.

194
00:10:25.090 --> 00:10:27.320
I am an enigma wrapped
in a badass riddle.

195
00:10:27.340 --> 00:10:29.450
- You got that. Boot?
- Yes. ma'am.

196
00:10:29.470 --> 00:10:30.570
Why are you 10-8?

197
00:10:30.600 --> 00:10:32.620
Uh. last shift
before I go on leave.

198
00:10:32.640 --> 00:10:34.740
I know... you should
be hiding under a desk

199
00:10:34.770 --> 00:10:37.500
until it is time to go
home. not out on the street.

200
00:10:37.520 --> 00:10:40.120
- Why?
- The curse of the last shift.

201
00:10:40.150 --> 00:10:42.830
- Did nothing I taught you stick?
- Only the rational bits.

202
00:10:42.860 --> 00:10:44.590
You see. Detective Harper feels

203
00:10:44.610 --> 00:10:47.030
that the last shift before
a vacation. a retirement.

204
00:10:47.060 --> 00:10:49.050
a wedding is to be feared.

205
00:10:49.070 --> 00:10:51.380
- She's very superstitious.
- I mean. so am I.

206
00:10:51.410 --> 00:10:53.010
I'm riding with you.

207
00:10:53.030 --> 00:10:54.890
Might as well write "collateral
damage" on my forehead.

208
00:10:54.910 --> 00:10:56.060
Why didn't you tell me?

209
00:10:56.080 --> 00:10:57.390
Because unlike
Detective Harper...

210
00:10:57.410 --> 00:10:58.770
I do not believe

211
00:10:58.790 --> 00:11:00.600
in superstitions or curses.

212
00:11:00.630 --> 00:11:03.770
Today is going to
be smooth sailing.

213
00:11:03.800 --> 00:11:04.860
Hey. Bailey. What's up?

214
00:11:04.890 --> 00:11:06.800
Uh. we have a huge problem.

215
00:11:07.880 --> 00:11:09.860
That's great. What's going on?

216
00:11:09.890 --> 00:11:11.150
Well. the wedding
planner came by

217
00:11:11.180 --> 00:11:12.360
to check her lighting setup

218
00:11:12.390 --> 00:11:14.650
and somehow shorted
out the HVAC system.

219
00:11:15.680 --> 00:11:17.330
It's getting hot in here.

220
00:11:17.350 --> 00:11:19.080
And it's supposed to be
even hotter this weekend.

221
00:11:19.100 --> 00:11:20.910
And if we don't have
air conditioning...

222
00:11:20.940 --> 00:11:22.420
Okay. we will. We
will. I can fix that.

223
00:11:22.440 --> 00:11:24.000
- Now?
- N-now?

224
00:11:24.020 --> 00:11:25.250
Uh. yes. No. yeah.

225
00:11:25.280 --> 00:11:26.710
She probably just
tripped a breaker.

226
00:11:26.740 --> 00:11:28.420
Look. we're about to
go back out on patrol.

227
00:11:28.450 --> 00:11:29.510
and we'll swing by.

228
00:11:29.530 --> 00:11:31.340
Okay. thank you.

229
00:11:31.360 --> 00:11:34.220
Is this a huge mistake.
doing the wedding here?

230
00:11:34.240 --> 00:11:36.550
No. No. this is
gonna be amazing.

231
00:11:36.580 --> 00:11:38.760
Come on. best wedding
ever. I promise.

232
00:11:38.790 --> 00:11:40.060
All right. I got
to go. I love you.

233
00:11:40.080 --> 00:11:41.180
- Everything okay?
- Yeah.

234
00:11:41.210 --> 00:11:45.270
No. perfect. It's
gonna be just. uh

235
00:11:45.300 --> 00:11:46.840
you know. just...
Juarez. let's go.

236
00:11:48.420 --> 00:11:49.940
Do we have to?

237
00:11:49.970 --> 00:11:51.650
I mean. there's plenty of
paperwork we could fill out.

238
00:11:51.680 --> 00:11:52.990
And I'm sure Sergeant Grey

239
00:11:53.010 --> 00:11:54.110
could find us things
to do at the station.

240
00:11:54.140 --> 00:11:55.780
- Thanks.
- Hmm.

241
00:11:55.810 --> 00:11:57.240
Hold your nerve. Officer Juarez.

242
00:11:57.270 --> 00:11:59.740
- That's an order.
- Yes. sir.

243
00:12:09.750 --> 00:12:11.010
Nice bike.

244
00:12:11.030 --> 00:12:12.760
Thank you.

245
00:12:12.780 --> 00:12:14.720
Doctor sign off
on you riding it?

246
00:12:14.740 --> 00:12:16.180
You mean. like. in writing?

247
00:12:16.200 --> 00:12:18.140
All I'm saying is.
is take it easy.

248
00:12:18.160 --> 00:12:20.430
It's your first day back.
and you're not 100% yet.

249
00:12:20.460 --> 00:12:22.020
Hell. I'm not even 100%.

250
00:12:22.040 --> 00:12:24.520
and I only had a baby.
not a near-death GSW.

251
00:12:24.540 --> 00:12:26.100
Yes. I will be
careful. I promise.

252
00:12:26.130 --> 00:12:27.520
- Good.
- Yeah.

253
00:12:27.550 --> 00:12:30.440
But the correct response
to my last sentence was.

254
00:12:30.470 --> 00:12:32.780
childbirth is deeply
traumatic to a woman's body

255
00:12:32.800 --> 00:12:34.570
and should never be minimized.

256
00:12:34.590 --> 00:12:37.490
Right. Got it.

257
00:12:37.510 --> 00:12:39.370
So. uh. how are you feeling?

258
00:12:39.390 --> 00:12:41.410
Mm. 80%.

259
00:12:41.430 --> 00:12:42.830
Sad to leave my baby

260
00:12:42.850 --> 00:12:44.710
but excited to use my
brain for something else.

261
00:12:44.730 --> 00:12:46.120
- You?
- Same

262
00:12:46.150 --> 00:12:47.830
e-except the. you
know. baby part.

263
00:12:47.860 --> 00:12:51.050
Yeah. I. um...

264
00:12:51.070 --> 00:12:53.170
I don't sleep well.

265
00:12:53.200 --> 00:12:55.170
Too many nightmares.

266
00:12:55.200 --> 00:12:57.390
But I'm hopeful that'll
change once we. uh.

267
00:12:57.410 --> 00:12:59.100
catch the crew
behind my shooting.

268
00:12:59.120 --> 00:13:00.680
- Any fresh leads?
- Not that I know of.

269
00:13:00.700 --> 00:13:02.640
but it's my first day too.

270
00:13:02.660 --> 00:13:03.980
All right. here's what we know.

271
00:13:04.000 --> 00:13:06.100
The Federal Reserve heist
was a two-pronged attack.

272
00:13:06.130 --> 00:13:07.650
In success. they
would have escaped

273
00:13:07.670 --> 00:13:09.440
with $30 million in
cash in an armored car.

274
00:13:09.460 --> 00:13:11.190
And we never would have
known about the secondary.

275
00:13:11.210 --> 00:13:12.650
much larger digital heist.

276
00:13:12.670 --> 00:13:14.490
While computer
forensics are ongoing.

277
00:13:14.510 --> 00:13:17.030
we've so far discovered
over a hundred million

278
00:13:17.050 --> 00:13:20.160
small-dollar transfers designed
to fly beneath the radar.

279
00:13:20.180 --> 00:13:22.280
Any progress on
identifying the crew

280
00:13:22.310 --> 00:13:24.620
that died at the scene?

281
00:13:24.640 --> 00:13:25.910
- No.
- How can that be?

282
00:13:25.940 --> 00:13:27.460
They were clearly
professional criminals.

283
00:13:27.480 --> 00:13:29.420
No prints or DNA
in any database.

284
00:13:29.440 --> 00:13:31.710
and social media scrub of
their faces turned up nothing.

285
00:13:31.740 --> 00:13:33.000
Our working theory is that

286
00:13:33.030 --> 00:13:34.800
a hacker sophisticated
enough to break through

287
00:13:34.820 --> 00:13:36.170
the Treasury Department firewalls

288
00:13:36.200 --> 00:13:38.010
could have purged
criminal histories

289
00:13:38.030 --> 00:13:39.970
from law-enforcement
databases prior to the heist.

290
00:13:39.990 --> 00:13:42.300
To sum it up. this
crew orchestrated

291
00:13:42.330 --> 00:13:43.970
a brutal attack on my people

292
00:13:44.000 --> 00:13:45.930
in order to rob the
Federal Reserve.

293
00:13:45.960 --> 00:13:47.940
killed three of their
own to slow us down.

294
00:13:47.960 --> 00:13:49.730
and there's no way to trace them

295
00:13:49.750 --> 00:13:50.860
or the fortune they stole?

296
00:13:50.880 --> 00:13:53.150
And given how rich they now are.

297
00:13:53.170 --> 00:13:54.860
they could be
anywhere in the world.

298
00:13:56.550 --> 00:14:00.110
All right. listen up. This
crew attacked our people

299
00:14:00.140 --> 00:14:02.200
in their homes.
killed six innocents.

300
00:14:02.220 --> 00:14:04.200
We won't let them
get away with this.

301
00:14:04.230 --> 00:14:08.620
The only way this ends
is bad guys in handcuffs.

302
00:14:08.650 --> 00:14:10.790
Hey. shouldn't you
be out on patrol?

303
00:14:10.820 --> 00:14:12.330
I'm stealing a few minutes

304
00:14:12.360 --> 00:14:13.960
to study for the detective's exam.

305
00:14:13.990 --> 00:14:15.710
I've been slammed
with so much OT.

306
00:14:15.740 --> 00:14:16.880
I've fallen way behind.

307
00:14:16.910 --> 00:14:19.880
Hey. can I ride with you today

308
00:14:19.910 --> 00:14:21.550
so you can quiz me
in between calls?

309
00:14:21.580 --> 00:14:23.800
Yeah. sure. But it's not
gonna solve your problem.

310
00:14:23.830 --> 00:14:25.600
I mean. if Lieutenant Primm
really has it out for you.

311
00:14:25.620 --> 00:14:26.850
he's not gonna follow

312
00:14:26.870 --> 00:14:28.390
the normal playbook
with your oral exam.

313
00:14:28.420 --> 00:14:30.230
He's gonna give you
some crazy scenarios.

314
00:14:30.250 --> 00:14:32.480
- try and sabotage you.
- That's not fair.

315
00:14:32.500 --> 00:14:34.230
The test should be the
same for everybody.

316
00:14:34.260 --> 00:14:36.070
How the hell am I supposed
to study for wild cards?

317
00:14:36.090 --> 00:14:37.780
You can't. I mean.
but we can spend today

318
00:14:37.800 --> 00:14:39.150
chasing outside-the-box calls.

319
00:14:39.180 --> 00:14:40.530
try and widen your
knowledge base a little.

320
00:14:40.550 --> 00:14:42.950
Okay. Thank you.

321
00:14:42.970 --> 00:14:45.120
Don't thank me yet. I'm
not gonna make today easy.

322
00:14:45.140 --> 00:14:46.620
I mean. the truth
is. you learn best

323
00:14:46.640 --> 00:14:48.200
when you're a little pissed off.

324
00:14:48.230 --> 00:14:50.210
Do I?
Or are you just trying

325
00:14:50.230 --> 00:14:52.290
to get me to give you
permission to be an ass?

326
00:14:52.320 --> 00:14:54.000
Well. if that's your attitude.

327
00:14:54.030 --> 00:14:55.750
- you really don't want my help.
- No. I do.

328
00:14:55.780 --> 00:14:58.210
I-I need it.

329
00:14:58.240 --> 00:15:00.800
Or do I?

330
00:15:00.820 --> 00:15:02.840
I don't like that smile.

331
00:15:02.870 --> 00:15:04.180
- That's my smile.
- Mm...

332
00:15:04.200 --> 00:15:06.180
If you're reading into
it. that's on you.

333
00:15:06.200 --> 00:15:08.180
Let's roll.

334
00:15:08.210 --> 00:15:11.310
Why do I feel like I'm
making a terrible mistake?

335
00:15:11.330 --> 00:15:13.690
Hey. Whoa! It is
an oven in here.

336
00:15:13.710 --> 00:15:14.980
I told you.

337
00:15:15.000 --> 00:15:18.320
- What if you can't fix it?
- I can fix it.

338
00:15:18.340 --> 00:15:21.030
Wedding is almost here.
Are you just so excited?

339
00:15:21.050 --> 00:15:22.740
- Totally.
- He just blew a breaker.

340
00:15:22.760 --> 00:15:24.740
I-I got a spare.
Don't worry about it.

341
00:15:24.760 --> 00:15:26.030
I mean. I'm made
of anxiety inside.

342
00:15:26.060 --> 00:15:28.540
but underneath that's
excitement. I think.

343
00:15:28.560 --> 00:15:30.160
Well. not to make it about me.

344
00:15:30.190 --> 00:15:31.620
but I just bought a sexy dress.

345
00:15:31.650 --> 00:15:33.540
and I'm ready to party.

346
00:15:33.570 --> 00:15:36.130
Yes.

347
00:15:36.150 --> 00:15:38.300
I fixed it 'cause I'm a genius.

348
00:15:38.320 --> 00:15:39.420
And humble.

349
00:15:39.450 --> 00:15:41.550
And icky. There we go.

350
00:15:41.570 --> 00:15:43.800
- All right. back to work.
- To taunt the curse some more.

351
00:15:43.830 --> 00:15:45.180
What curse?

352
00:15:45.200 --> 00:15:46.800
Why would you say that
in front of Bailey?

353
00:15:46.830 --> 00:15:48.220
- I'm sorry. sir.
- It's n... it's nothing.

354
00:15:48.250 --> 00:15:50.600
It's a Harper superstition.
curse of the last shift.

355
00:15:50.620 --> 00:15:52.600
I... nothing is
gonna go wrong today.

356
00:15:52.630 --> 00:15:55.020
Okay? I promise.

357
00:15:55.040 --> 00:15:56.810
- Whoa.
- Hey. How can I help you?

358
00:15:56.840 --> 00:15:58.730
Hi. Yeah. uh. Josh Randall.

359
00:15:58.760 --> 00:16:00.900
I just bought the
house next door.

360
00:16:00.930 --> 00:16:02.900
The police. Is...
is there a problem?

361
00:16:02.930 --> 00:16:04.740
Oh. no. not at all. I'm
Bailey. and this is John.

362
00:16:04.760 --> 00:16:06.320
- We live here.
- Oh. cool.

363
00:16:06.350 --> 00:16:08.280
I've never had a cop
for a neighbor before.

364
00:16:08.310 --> 00:16:10.490
Uh. anyway. I just wanted to
stop by and bring you this.

365
00:16:10.520 --> 00:16:12.290
- Oh. that's so nice.
- Very sweet.

366
00:16:12.310 --> 00:16:13.870
But we should be
the ones giving you

367
00:16:13.900 --> 00:16:15.120
the "welcome to the
neighborhood" bottle.

368
00:16:15.150 --> 00:16:17.380
Well. it's not exactly
a "welcome" bottle.

369
00:16:17.400 --> 00:16:20.050
It's more of a "sorry for
the inconvenience" bottle.

370
00:16:20.070 --> 00:16:21.420
I'm tearing down the house
next door this weekend.

371
00:16:21.450 --> 00:16:24.340
and it's possible it might
get a little... little noisy.

372
00:16:24.370 --> 00:16:25.970
- No. No. no. no. he ca...
- Okay. no. no. I... I...

373
00:16:25.990 --> 00:16:27.430
I got... I got... I got it.

374
00:16:27.450 --> 00:16:30.640
We're actually getting
married this weekend... here.

375
00:16:30.660 --> 00:16:32.790
Yikes.

376
00:16:34.290 --> 00:16:35.850
Wish I had brought a
pricier bottle of champagne.

377
00:16:35.880 --> 00:16:37.270
Yeah. we're gonna have to just

378
00:16:37.300 --> 00:16:38.520
push back that demolition.

379
00:16:38.550 --> 00:16:40.110
Oh. yeah. totally.

380
00:16:40.130 --> 00:16:41.280
But there's no way.

381
00:16:41.300 --> 00:16:42.900
Sorry. the permits
have all been pulled.

382
00:16:42.930 --> 00:16:44.490
and my contractor has
a super-tight window

383
00:16:44.510 --> 00:16:45.820
to get the work done.

384
00:16:45.850 --> 00:16:47.910
and I'm just not able
to alter my schedule

385
00:16:47.930 --> 00:16:50.700
not <i>not</i> able. just. uh.

386
00:16:50.730 --> 00:16:52.290
you know. not going to.

387
00:16:52.310 --> 00:16:53.950
You get it. It's
what I was gonna do

388
00:16:53.980 --> 00:16:56.580
and am gonna do.
but. um. anyway. I'm

389
00:16:56.610 --> 00:16:59.340
oof... just gutted
about the mix-up.

390
00:16:59.360 --> 00:17:01.750
It's. um... it'll be
a fun story. right?

391
00:17:01.780 --> 00:17:03.840
"Three bulldozers
at our wedding."

392
00:17:03.860 --> 00:17:06.800
Anyway. see you this weekend.

393
00:17:06.820 --> 00:17:09.760
Hoo. Curse of the last shift.

394
00:17:14.750 --> 00:17:16.600
I'm... I'm... I'm gonna...

395
00:17:16.630 --> 00:17:19.250
I'm... I'm... I'm
gonna... I'm just...

396
00:17:39.860 --> 00:17:41.130
Welcome back. Officer Thorsen.

397
00:17:41.150 --> 00:17:43.340
Thank you. sir.
and. um. thank you

398
00:17:43.360 --> 00:17:45.010
for everything you did for
me while on medical leave.

399
00:17:45.030 --> 00:17:47.970
You're welcome. but
that kindness stopped

400
00:17:47.990 --> 00:17:49.590
when you put that uniform
back on this morning.

401
00:17:49.620 --> 00:17:50.930
Sir?

402
00:17:50.950 --> 00:17:52.390
I've been where you are. son

403
00:17:52.410 --> 00:17:54.010
trying to come back
after being shot.

404
00:17:54.040 --> 00:17:55.890
almost dying.

405
00:17:55.920 --> 00:17:57.230
I would be doing you no kindness

406
00:17:57.250 --> 00:17:58.440
by coddling you now.

407
00:17:58.460 --> 00:17:59.810
Yes. sir. Look.
I'm... I'm not looking

408
00:17:59.840 --> 00:18:01.060
for any special treatment.
I'm ready to get

409
00:18:01.090 --> 00:18:02.520
back on the street
and prove myself.

410
00:18:02.550 --> 00:18:04.440
That's not your
decision to make.

411
00:18:04.470 --> 00:18:06.110
I'm assigning you
to station duties

412
00:18:06.130 --> 00:18:08.400
while you start seeing the
department psychiatrist.

413
00:18:08.430 --> 00:18:11.200
Only after they approve
you for active duty

414
00:18:11.220 --> 00:18:12.620
will I put you
back on the street.

415
00:18:12.640 --> 00:18:14.120
Sir. with all due respect.

416
00:18:14.140 --> 00:18:16.870
I'm already seeing a
pretty dope therapist.

417
00:18:16.890 --> 00:18:18.160
I mean. Lil' Gurkin
swears by him.

418
00:18:18.190 --> 00:18:19.500
- Who the hell is Lil' Gurkin?
- He's a...

419
00:18:19.520 --> 00:18:21.250
Y-you know what? I don't care.

420
00:18:21.270 --> 00:18:23.420
The department requires you
to see <i>their</i> psychiatrist.

421
00:18:23.440 --> 00:18:25.050
You're going.

422
00:18:25.070 --> 00:18:27.280
Twice a week. First
appointment's tonight.

423
00:18:30.870 --> 00:18:32.590
- There you are.
- Hey. mama.

424
00:18:32.620 --> 00:18:34.640
Welcome back.

425
00:18:34.660 --> 00:18:36.310
You just got a call from BHPD.

426
00:18:36.330 --> 00:18:38.350
Some guy wrapped his
half-million-dollar Lambo

427
00:18:38.370 --> 00:18:40.270
- around a tree in Beverly Hills.
- And I care why?

428
00:18:40.290 --> 00:18:42.020
Because you had his
fingerprints flagged

429
00:18:42.050 --> 00:18:44.060
in the system with
no name associated.

430
00:18:44.090 --> 00:18:45.440
Hot damn. And where is he now?

431
00:18:45.470 --> 00:18:47.230
Landing at the hospital.
Why? Who is this guy?

432
00:18:47.260 --> 00:18:50.490
We got a hit on our
Federal Reserve crew.

433
00:18:50.510 --> 00:18:53.410
- Sir. I would like to go...
- Absolutely not.

434
00:18:57.190 --> 00:18:59.290
MVA with contusions to forehead.

435
00:18:59.310 --> 00:19:02.120
possible fracture
to left humerus.

436
00:19:02.150 --> 00:19:03.580
And one. two. three.

437
00:19:06.440 --> 00:19:07.800
Page Dr. Hoffman.
He's gonna need

438
00:19:07.820 --> 00:19:09.720
a surgical consult on his arm.

439
00:19:09.740 --> 00:19:11.010
Is my Lambo okay?

440
00:19:11.030 --> 00:19:12.220
It's brand-new.

441
00:19:12.240 --> 00:19:13.720
I just drove it off
the lot today...

442
00:19:13.740 --> 00:19:15.010
And right into a tree.

443
00:19:15.040 --> 00:19:16.010
Relax.

444
00:19:18.750 --> 00:19:19.890
Hello.

445
00:19:19.920 --> 00:19:21.850
This is Detective Harper. LAPD.

446
00:19:21.880 --> 00:19:23.730
The man you just brought
into the hospital is wanted

447
00:19:23.750 --> 00:19:25.150
for murder. armed robbery.

448
00:19:25.170 --> 00:19:26.860
<i>and assault on
law-enforcement officers.</i>

449
00:19:26.880 --> 00:19:28.400
<i>He is extremely dangerous.</i>

450
00:19:32.720 --> 00:19:34.390
Oh!

451
00:19:49.070 --> 00:19:50.380
What's the situation?

452
00:19:50.410 --> 00:19:52.130
He's got a hostage in
there. She's a nurse.

453
00:19:52.160 --> 00:19:54.090
I thought I had a clear
shot. but I hit her.

454
00:19:54.120 --> 00:19:55.390
What kind of weapon has he got?

455
00:19:55.410 --> 00:19:56.600
It's a blade. some
kind of scalpel.

456
00:19:56.620 --> 00:19:57.810
It's Lisa. She's gut shot.

457
00:19:57.830 --> 00:19:58.930
We got to get her
out of there fast.

458
00:19:58.960 --> 00:20:00.390
Okay. this is gonna be tricky.

459
00:20:00.420 --> 00:20:01.980
We have no idea who this guy is

460
00:20:02.000 --> 00:20:03.440
or what his pressure points are.

461
00:20:03.460 --> 00:20:05.150
We push the wrong one. he
could snap and kill her.

462
00:20:05.170 --> 00:20:06.560
We don't got time
to analyze him.

463
00:20:06.590 --> 00:20:08.230
I think I can get a clean shot

464
00:20:08.260 --> 00:20:09.650
if Nolan can get him
focused on the door.

465
00:20:09.670 --> 00:20:11.590
If it goes sideways.
I'll take the shot.

466
00:20:13.680 --> 00:20:15.360
All right. do it.

467
00:20:15.390 --> 00:20:16.280
Hey. turn off the lights.

468
00:20:16.310 --> 00:20:17.640
Yes. sir.

469
00:20:23.020 --> 00:20:24.710
Sir. this is our first
lead in six weeks.

470
00:20:24.730 --> 00:20:26.080
If he ends up dead...

471
00:20:26.110 --> 00:20:27.790
Our priority is the
hostage. always.

472
00:20:27.820 --> 00:20:28.630
No. yes. of course. I just...

473
00:20:28.650 --> 00:20:29.780
Sir?

474
00:20:30.900 --> 00:20:33.170
I'm Officer John Nolan. LAPD.

475
00:20:33.200 --> 00:20:34.260
We need to talk.

476
00:20:34.280 --> 00:20:36.510
About what. how screwed I am?

477
00:20:36.530 --> 00:20:37.930
Or how you're gonna
offer me a ride

478
00:20:37.950 --> 00:20:40.430
to a non-extradition country
if I let the hostage go?

479
00:20:40.460 --> 00:20:43.100
I think we should focus on
not making matters any worse.

480
00:20:43.120 --> 00:20:44.440
You both need medical attention.

481
00:20:44.460 --> 00:20:45.770
Let me get that for you.

482
00:20:47.300 --> 00:20:48.980
Look. man. you're a smart guy.

483
00:20:49.010 --> 00:20:51.530
You know there's a deal
to be made if you help us.

484
00:20:51.550 --> 00:20:53.900
Forget it. I'm not a rat.

485
00:20:53.930 --> 00:20:56.280
Even if I was. I'd never
survive long enough for WITSEC.

486
00:20:56.300 --> 00:20:58.070
That's not true.
We can protect you.

487
00:20:58.100 --> 00:20:59.660
No. you can't.

488
00:21:02.060 --> 00:21:03.950
You can't.

489
00:21:03.980 --> 00:21:06.420
I should never have
bought that stupid car.

490
00:21:06.440 --> 00:21:07.900
He wa... he warned me.

491
00:21:10.030 --> 00:21:12.630
And I'm gonna die.

492
00:21:12.650 --> 00:21:14.590
But first. I'm
gonna make it hurt.

493
00:21:27.500 --> 00:21:29.100
- Clear.
- Hey.

494
00:21:29.130 --> 00:21:30.270
Come on!

495
00:21:30.300 --> 00:21:32.020
- Keep pressure on that.
- I know.

496
00:21:32.050 --> 00:21:32.980
Right. Ready?

497
00:21:33.010 --> 00:21:34.610
Come on. There we go.

498
00:21:34.630 --> 00:21:35.760
Get her out. Get her out.

499
00:21:39.350 --> 00:21:40.990
- What now?
- Now we hope

500
00:21:41.020 --> 00:21:42.780
that the address on his
registration is real

501
00:21:42.810 --> 00:21:45.330
and he left something behind
that'll lead us to his crew.

502
00:21:49.650 --> 00:21:52.540
Hey. I'm gonna need your
weapon for OIS investigation.

503
00:21:54.400 --> 00:21:57.470
Hey. You okay?

504
00:21:57.490 --> 00:21:59.050
Better than him.

505
00:21:59.080 --> 00:22:01.470
Mm. Maybe I should have asked

506
00:22:01.490 --> 00:22:03.260
Harper or Lopez
to help me study.

507
00:22:03.290 --> 00:22:05.020
Eh. Harper's busy
with the task force.

508
00:22:05.040 --> 00:22:06.980
and Lopez's cop brain
is just booting up.

509
00:22:07.000 --> 00:22:09.730
Look. the truth is. all
ranked police officers

510
00:22:09.750 --> 00:22:11.150
share the same knowledge base.

511
00:22:11.170 --> 00:22:12.810
I mean. sergeant.
lieutenant. detective.

512
00:22:12.840 --> 00:22:14.900
there's only about 8%
unique to each specialty.

513
00:22:14.920 --> 00:22:17.070
Yeah. right. but it's that 8%

514
00:22:17.090 --> 00:22:18.700
where Primm will
try and trip me up.

515
00:22:18.720 --> 00:22:20.660
Maybe. but I'd argue

516
00:22:20.680 --> 00:22:22.410
that's exactly what
he wants you to think.

517
00:22:22.430 --> 00:22:23.740
Great.

518
00:22:23.770 --> 00:22:25.120
Yeah. thank you
so much for that.

519
00:22:25.140 --> 00:22:27.410
Thank you. Now I get to play

520
00:22:27.440 --> 00:22:29.750
the second-guessing game
where I spiral out of control

521
00:22:29.770 --> 00:22:32.040
worrying about whether
or not Primm knows

522
00:22:32.070 --> 00:22:34.090
that I think he will
try and trip me up

523
00:22:34.110 --> 00:22:36.050
and that I'm focusing
on the wild cards

524
00:22:36.070 --> 00:22:37.550
while he circles
back to all the stuff

525
00:22:37.570 --> 00:22:38.880
I should be studying.

526
00:22:38.910 --> 00:22:41.300
making me look like an
idiot at the oral exam.

527
00:22:41.330 --> 00:22:43.470
pushing me so far down
the promotions list

528
00:22:43.490 --> 00:22:48.100
that even if I do manage
to pass the oral exam

529
00:22:48.120 --> 00:22:52.230
oh. my gosh. I will never
even qualify for an open slot.

530
00:22:52.250 --> 00:22:54.310
This is great.

531
00:22:54.340 --> 00:22:55.720
Great.

532
00:22:58.880 --> 00:23:00.650
- Please don't.
- I didn't say anything.

533
00:23:00.680 --> 00:23:02.740
I can hear you.
Y-you're thinking it.

534
00:23:02.760 --> 00:23:04.240
Just

535
00:23:04.270 --> 00:23:05.830
okay. new idea

536
00:23:05.850 --> 00:23:07.910
unique scenarios during the day.

537
00:23:07.940 --> 00:23:10.460
study manual at night.

538
00:23:10.480 --> 00:23:11.860
I will sleep when it's over.

539
00:23:24.740 --> 00:23:26.220
- Clear.
- Clear.

540
00:23:26.250 --> 00:23:28.020
Clear.

541
00:23:28.040 --> 00:23:30.560
All right. we're gonna
have to move fast.

542
00:23:30.580 --> 00:23:32.390
Any evidence our suspect
might have left behind

543
00:23:32.420 --> 00:23:34.560
is gonna be useless the very
second his crew finds out

544
00:23:34.590 --> 00:23:35.980
he was killed by cops.

545
00:23:36.010 --> 00:23:37.520
Officer Juarez. what
is our next move?

546
00:23:37.550 --> 00:23:38.690
Well. place is a rental.

547
00:23:38.720 --> 00:23:40.360
clearly not the
suspect's main domicile.

548
00:23:40.380 --> 00:23:43.160
So we tear the house apart
in a top-to-bottom search

549
00:23:43.180 --> 00:23:45.950
while trying to avoid provoking
the curse any further.

550
00:23:45.970 --> 00:23:48.330
- That's...
- Wh... uh. what curse?

551
00:23:48.350 --> 00:23:49.410
It's nothing.

552
00:23:49.440 --> 00:23:50.830
Last shift before the wedding.

553
00:23:50.850 --> 00:23:52.330
Yeah. I don't mess with curses.

554
00:23:52.360 --> 00:23:55.540
Not since Uncle Cheese
uncovered that ancient tomb.

555
00:23:55.570 --> 00:23:57.630
You can keep your bad juju.

556
00:23:57.650 --> 00:24:01.170
"Final Destination" karma
target away from me.

557
00:24:01.200 --> 00:24:02.550
Okay.

558
00:24:02.570 --> 00:24:04.220
Thank you.

559
00:24:04.240 --> 00:24:05.640
All right. Officer Juarez.
let's start our search

560
00:24:05.660 --> 00:24:08.100
in the back bedroom. where
you will recite for me

561
00:24:08.120 --> 00:24:09.680
the five rules of
a domicile search

562
00:24:09.710 --> 00:24:11.430
in backwards alphabetical order.

563
00:24:11.460 --> 00:24:13.480
Any mistakes you make will
result in a blue page.

564
00:24:13.500 --> 00:24:15.900
If you mention the word
"curse" in my presence again.

565
00:24:15.920 --> 00:24:18.150
you'll be volunteered for
all the cavity searches

566
00:24:18.170 --> 00:24:20.070
at the station from now
until your 30th birthday.

567
00:24:20.090 --> 00:24:21.280
Yes. sir.

568
00:24:21.300 --> 00:24:22.070
Thank you.

569
00:24:22.090 --> 00:24:23.360
Clear.

570
00:24:28.850 --> 00:24:31.040
7-Metro-100. I'm on
the scene of a 187.

571
00:24:31.060 --> 00:24:33.040
Assigning control
to Officer Chen.

572
00:24:33.060 --> 00:24:34.920
All right. I'm
here as a resource.

573
00:24:34.940 --> 00:24:36.670
But as of now. you're in charge.

574
00:24:36.690 --> 00:24:38.210
What's your first move?

575
00:24:38.230 --> 00:24:40.210
Crime scene's too small.

576
00:24:40.240 --> 00:24:42.630
Responding officers didn't
recover the murder weapon.

577
00:24:42.660 --> 00:24:45.630
Shooter probably ditched it
somewhere along the block.

578
00:24:45.660 --> 00:24:46.780
Make the call.

579
00:24:48.540 --> 00:24:51.010
7-Metro-100 requesting
additional units

580
00:24:51.040 --> 00:24:53.810
for an expanded crime scene.
canvass. and search grid.

581
00:24:53.830 --> 00:24:56.480
Notify Homicide and
mobilize the TID team.

582
00:24:56.500 --> 00:24:59.230
What else?

583
00:24:59.260 --> 00:25:01.190
I mean. there's nothing else
we can do until TID gets here

584
00:25:01.220 --> 00:25:03.150
to document the scene.

585
00:25:03.180 --> 00:25:04.490
Am I missing something?

586
00:25:04.510 --> 00:25:06.490
Do you think you're
missing something?

587
00:25:06.510 --> 00:25:09.990
I think you're messing with me.

588
00:25:10.020 --> 00:25:14.370
Un... unless you're not. and
I am really missing something.

589
00:25:14.400 --> 00:25:15.580
All right. well. you've
checked all the obvious boxes.

590
00:25:15.600 --> 00:25:17.120
but there's a wild card.

591
00:25:17.150 --> 00:25:18.330
Do you want me to
tell you what it is?

592
00:25:18.360 --> 00:25:19.750
Yes. No.

593
00:25:19.780 --> 00:25:21.170
Just let me think for a minute.

594
00:25:21.190 --> 00:25:22.800
All right. pretend you
don't have a minute.

595
00:25:22.820 --> 00:25:24.130
What are you missing?

596
00:25:24.160 --> 00:25:26.340
Nothing.

597
00:25:26.370 --> 00:25:28.010
Something? What is it?

598
00:25:28.030 --> 00:25:29.180
No. don't tell me. Just...

599
00:25:29.200 --> 00:25:30.470
Look. there's no
shame in not knowing

600
00:25:30.490 --> 00:25:32.010
- the answer. Officer Chen.
- Just let me think

601
00:25:32.040 --> 00:25:34.520
for a minute. Sergeant
Bradford. please.

602
00:25:36.960 --> 00:25:38.790
What is that?

603
00:25:41.340 --> 00:25:43.110
The thing you should
have thought of.

604
00:25:43.130 --> 00:25:45.440
No. we have to turn this off.
How are we gonna turn it off?

605
00:25:45.470 --> 00:25:47.240
Ugh.

606
00:25:49.720 --> 00:25:50.740
Oh. my gosh.

607
00:25:52.850 --> 00:25:54.290
No.

608
00:26:13.910 --> 00:26:16.430
Hey. You need anything?

609
00:26:16.460 --> 00:26:18.100
Uh. no.

610
00:26:18.130 --> 00:26:21.650
The union rep is on his way.
and IA is landing in 30.

611
00:26:21.670 --> 00:26:26.110
Having Grey as a
witness is a godsend.

612
00:26:26.130 --> 00:26:28.450
Any one of us would
have taken the shot.

613
00:26:28.470 --> 00:26:30.110
You saved Lisa's life.

614
00:26:30.140 --> 00:26:32.490
I know. but I'm still gonna
have nightmares about it.

615
00:26:32.520 --> 00:26:34.200
even though I've been
through it before.

616
00:26:34.230 --> 00:26:35.660
Can I do anything more to help?

617
00:26:35.680 --> 00:26:37.200
- Call James?
- No.

618
00:26:37.230 --> 00:26:39.620
No. not yet.

619
00:26:39.650 --> 00:26:41.790
I know he's gonna be mad at me
for not telling him right away.

620
00:26:41.820 --> 00:26:44.880
but there's a part of him
that is gonna judge me.

621
00:26:44.900 --> 00:26:48.050
and I'm just... I'm not ready
to deal with that right now.

622
00:26:48.070 --> 00:26:50.880
I come bearing
burritos and babies.

623
00:26:50.910 --> 00:26:52.550
Ooh. I don't know which
I'm happier to see.

624
00:26:52.580 --> 00:26:53.620
Well...

625
00:26:55.000 --> 00:26:57.560
- Don't judge me.
- I would never.

626
00:26:57.580 --> 00:26:58.980
I heard what happened.

627
00:26:59.000 --> 00:27:01.060
- Sounds like a clean shoot.
- Thank you.

628
00:27:01.090 --> 00:27:03.360
Aw. sweet. sweet baby.

629
00:27:03.380 --> 00:27:04.400
First station visit.

630
00:27:04.420 --> 00:27:05.820
- That is exciting.
- Mm-hmm.

631
00:27:05.840 --> 00:27:08.150
- Yeah.
- Here you go.

632
00:27:08.180 --> 00:27:09.280
Aw.

633
00:27:09.300 --> 00:27:11.820
That is so cute. Thank you.

634
00:27:11.850 --> 00:27:13.570
Slow day at the front desk?

635
00:27:13.600 --> 00:27:14.780
- Glacial.
- Mm.

636
00:27:14.810 --> 00:27:16.160
At this point. I'm
looking forward

637
00:27:16.180 --> 00:27:17.910
- to department-mandated therapy.
- Mm. don't.

638
00:27:17.940 --> 00:27:19.870
In-house shrinks
are a unique breed.

639
00:27:19.900 --> 00:27:22.040
Most are ancient
or uninterested.

640
00:27:22.060 --> 00:27:23.880
And. legally. they
don't work for you.

641
00:27:23.900 --> 00:27:25.630
You got to stay vigilant.
Don't over share.

642
00:27:25.650 --> 00:27:26.690
Okay.

643
00:27:28.360 --> 00:27:30.090
Uh. excuse me.

644
00:27:30.110 --> 00:27:32.180
That could not have
backfired more spectacularly.

645
00:27:32.200 --> 00:27:34.510
It was a literal clown show.

646
00:27:34.540 --> 00:27:36.140
Hopefully nobody heard about it.

647
00:27:44.750 --> 00:27:46.730
Okay. that's very funny.

648
00:27:46.760 --> 00:27:48.820
Thank you.

649
00:27:48.840 --> 00:27:50.650
Hey. welcome back.
Officer Thorsen.

650
00:27:50.680 --> 00:27:51.860
Thank you. sir. It's
good to be back.

651
00:27:51.890 --> 00:27:53.410
It's really good to see you.

652
00:27:53.430 --> 00:27:55.910
Hey. um. does everybody know
about what happened to me?

653
00:27:55.930 --> 00:27:57.910
Oh. you mean the clown show?

654
00:27:57.930 --> 00:27:59.540
Yeah. everyone.

655
00:27:59.560 --> 00:28:00.870
Um. meanwhile. I ran

656
00:28:00.890 --> 00:28:02.210
a background check
on your victim...

657
00:28:02.230 --> 00:28:04.370
Claude Smith. 36.

658
00:28:04.400 --> 00:28:07.920
professional clown/
mime/barista.

659
00:28:07.940 --> 00:28:10.550
No priors. Closest
family's in Arizona.

660
00:28:10.570 --> 00:28:12.010
And he lives right around the
corner from where he was shot.

661
00:28:12.030 --> 00:28:13.170
Th-that's great.
Thank you so much.

662
00:28:13.200 --> 00:28:15.760
Uh... Wesley. hey.

663
00:28:15.780 --> 00:28:17.970
Sorry. Oh. my gosh.

664
00:28:18.000 --> 00:28:20.020
Um. I really need your
professional opinion.

665
00:28:20.040 --> 00:28:21.560
Uh-uh. No. I'm on
paternity leave.

666
00:28:21.580 --> 00:28:23.350
Oh. wait. so does that mean

667
00:28:23.380 --> 00:28:26.810
you didn't hear about
my... clown show?

668
00:28:26.840 --> 00:28:28.650
No. no. no. I heard.

669
00:28:28.670 --> 00:28:30.480
Your crime scene was
fatally compromised.

670
00:28:30.510 --> 00:28:32.320
The only way for you to
guarantee a conviction

671
00:28:32.340 --> 00:28:34.030
is to get a full
confession from the killer

672
00:28:34.050 --> 00:28:35.450
that's if you can find them.

673
00:28:35.470 --> 00:28:36.600
So good luck.

674
00:28:37.850 --> 00:28:38.830
Great.

675
00:28:38.850 --> 00:28:41.370
Sir. again. I'm...

676
00:28:41.390 --> 00:28:44.540
I'm very sorry about
focusing too much on the

677
00:28:44.560 --> 00:28:46.710
the baseless superstition.

678
00:28:46.730 --> 00:28:49.920
It's just in my DNA to take
these things seriously.

679
00:28:49.940 --> 00:28:52.010
Okay. it's not about
taking them seriously.

680
00:28:52.030 --> 00:28:54.130
It's about allowing
them to distract you.

681
00:28:54.160 --> 00:28:55.800
You've been on the job
long enough to know

682
00:28:55.820 --> 00:28:58.300
what can happen when you lose
focus. even for a moment.

683
00:28:58.330 --> 00:28:59.660
Yes. sir.

684
00:29:09.880 --> 00:29:11.300
Whoa. Sir.

685
00:29:12.800 --> 00:29:13.880
Whoa.

686
00:29:17.050 --> 00:29:18.570
There's only one number
in the call history.

687
00:29:18.600 --> 00:29:20.280
Looks like a daily check-in

688
00:29:20.310 --> 00:29:23.370
at 4:00 p.m.

689
00:29:23.390 --> 00:29:25.250
That gives us exactly
two hours to figure out

690
00:29:25.270 --> 00:29:27.210
what we're gonna do the
next time that phone rings.

691
00:29:32.530 --> 00:29:34.960
We got a warrant on an
incoming phone call.

692
00:29:34.990 --> 00:29:37.470
Audio and visual tap
of the suspect's phone.

693
00:29:37.490 --> 00:29:39.260
What's that noise?

694
00:29:39.280 --> 00:29:40.510
Sounds industrial.

695
00:29:40.540 --> 00:29:41.850
Yeah. or mechanical.

696
00:29:41.870 --> 00:29:43.470
Where's the visual?
Do we have it...

697
00:29:43.500 --> 00:29:44.770
Working on it. It
takes a little longer

698
00:29:44.790 --> 00:29:46.890
to activate the phone's camera.

699
00:29:46.920 --> 00:29:48.040
There we go.

700
00:29:49.590 --> 00:29:51.060
They're on a plane.

701
00:29:51.090 --> 00:29:52.650
Yeah. it looks private.

702
00:29:52.670 --> 00:29:54.280
Oh. that's a G550.

703
00:29:54.300 --> 00:29:57.030
It's an older model. 2012 maybe.

704
00:29:57.050 --> 00:29:59.280
You can tell that just by
looking at the ceiling?

705
00:29:59.300 --> 00:30:01.910
Let's just say I. uh. spent
some quality horizontal time

706
00:30:01.930 --> 00:30:03.370
on one of those
on a trip to Rome

707
00:30:03.390 --> 00:30:04.830
with an Italian supermodel.

708
00:30:04.850 --> 00:30:07.250
- Don't judge.
- Oh. I'm judging.

709
00:30:07.270 --> 00:30:09.460
Okay. so all we have to do is
figure out where they're flying

710
00:30:09.480 --> 00:30:11.080
and then have law
enforcement waiting for them.

711
00:30:11.110 --> 00:30:13.090
It's impossible to
get a precise location

712
00:30:13.110 --> 00:30:15.130
with a phone that's
flying at 30.000 feet.

713
00:30:15.150 --> 00:30:17.420
But if we can get a
rough GPS when it calls.

714
00:30:17.450 --> 00:30:19.510
they might be able to match
it to the plane's transponder.

715
00:30:19.530 --> 00:30:21.050
I hate to rain on this parade.

716
00:30:21.080 --> 00:30:24.100
but we don't know for
sure that our crew

717
00:30:24.120 --> 00:30:25.180
is on the other
end of that phone.

718
00:30:25.210 --> 00:30:26.930
It could be the hostage
taker's girlfriend.

719
00:30:26.960 --> 00:30:28.560
his drug dealer.

720
00:30:28.580 --> 00:30:30.730
We need confirmation to
get an arrest warrant.

721
00:30:30.750 --> 00:30:32.730
We got a more immediate problem.

722
00:30:32.760 --> 00:30:34.570
That phone is gonna call
this phone in four minutes.

723
00:30:34.590 --> 00:30:35.980
And whoever is on that
plane is gonna know

724
00:30:36.010 --> 00:30:38.190
they're not talking
to their guy.

725
00:30:38.220 --> 00:30:39.400
Unless...

726
00:30:46.640 --> 00:30:48.750
Ten seconds.

727
00:30:48.770 --> 00:30:51.370
Right.

728
00:31:12.540 --> 00:31:13.920
Here we go.

729
00:31:23.390 --> 00:31:25.160
Yo.

730
00:31:25.180 --> 00:31:26.410
Wow. that thing sounds

731
00:31:26.430 --> 00:31:27.950
even more obnoxious
than I thought it would.

732
00:31:27.980 --> 00:31:30.120
Yeah. it kicks
ass. Where are you?

733
00:31:30.150 --> 00:31:32.540
Just crossed out of
Mexican airspace.

734
00:31:32.560 --> 00:31:34.250
<i>So what'd you find
out about the place?</i>

735
00:31:38.990 --> 00:31:40.260
<i>Banks?</i>

736
00:31:40.280 --> 00:31:43.840
Eh... it... if... ah... money.

737
00:31:43.870 --> 00:31:45.680
What? Banks. you're breaking up.

738
00:31:45.700 --> 00:31:48.390
Wi... he... but...
y... if... you

739
00:31:48.410 --> 00:31:49.960
eh... I... it... uh...

740
00:31:51.460 --> 00:31:54.100
- Think he bought it?
- We'll find out.

741
00:31:54.130 --> 00:31:56.310
- Lost him?
- Yeah.

742
00:31:56.340 --> 00:31:59.070
But before that.
he sounded weird.

743
00:31:59.090 --> 00:32:01.110
You think something's up?

744
00:32:01.130 --> 00:32:03.110
I don't know.

745
00:32:03.140 --> 00:32:04.850
But better safe than sorry.

746
00:32:07.470 --> 00:32:09.620
- Damn it.
- What's happening?

747
00:32:09.640 --> 00:32:12.210
They destroyed the phone. They
didn't quite buy your act.

748
00:32:12.230 --> 00:32:14.370
Did you connect the phone
GPS to the plane transponder?

749
00:32:14.400 --> 00:32:15.750
Working on it.

750
00:32:15.770 --> 00:32:18.840
Oh. We got facial matches.

751
00:32:18.860 --> 00:32:20.840
He's Boyd Taylor. and
the two women with him

752
00:32:20.860 --> 00:32:23.550
are Cyesha Witt and Kim Loncar.

753
00:32:23.570 --> 00:32:25.340
All have bodies on them

754
00:32:25.370 --> 00:32:27.180
in connection with a previous
series of armed robberies

755
00:32:27.200 --> 00:32:28.970
- across four states.
- There's our confirmation.

756
00:32:29.000 --> 00:32:30.560
Got the transponder.

757
00:32:30.580 --> 00:32:32.980
Jet's flying from
Mexico City to LAX.

758
00:32:33.000 --> 00:32:34.690
Wait. they just filed

759
00:32:34.710 --> 00:32:36.440
a new flight plan
to land at Whittier.

760
00:32:36.460 --> 00:32:38.690
They're pivoting in case
we're waiting for them at LAX.

761
00:32:38.710 --> 00:32:40.610
Let's mount up. people.

762
00:32:40.630 --> 00:32:42.740
Sir. we should really
sit this one out.

763
00:32:42.760 --> 00:32:43.740
No way.

764
00:32:43.760 --> 00:32:45.070
She's right.

765
00:32:45.100 --> 00:32:46.780
It's your last shift.
You should stay here.

766
00:32:46.810 --> 00:32:48.410
Sir. all due respect. no.

767
00:32:48.430 --> 00:32:51.410
This guy ambushed my friends
and sent a killer to my house.

768
00:32:51.440 --> 00:32:53.850
I need to see this
through. last shift or no.

769
00:32:55.230 --> 00:32:56.670
Okay.

770
00:32:56.690 --> 00:32:59.340
But you're not riding with us.

771
00:32:59.360 --> 00:33:00.780
- Sir...
- No.

772
00:33:09.490 --> 00:33:12.430
What are we doing?

773
00:33:12.460 --> 00:33:14.100
Thinking.

774
00:33:14.120 --> 00:33:15.960
Hmm. Feels like we're sitting.

775
00:33:18.340 --> 00:33:20.770
The search of the victim's
house turned up nothing.

776
00:33:20.800 --> 00:33:22.860
Family and friends gave
us no possible motives

777
00:33:22.880 --> 00:33:24.690
for why someone would kill him.

778
00:33:24.720 --> 00:33:26.800
And with no forensics. I...

779
00:33:29.140 --> 00:33:31.120
I think I should skip
the detective's exam.

780
00:33:31.140 --> 00:33:32.450
- Lucy.
- I am not ready.

781
00:33:32.480 --> 00:33:34.080
No. you are ready.

782
00:33:34.100 --> 00:33:35.460
Don't let Primm
get in your head.

783
00:33:35.480 --> 00:33:36.540
That ship sailed this morning.

784
00:33:36.560 --> 00:33:38.370
Look. I-I know myself.

785
00:33:38.400 --> 00:33:41.250
If I take this test and I
fail. it'll kill my confidence.

786
00:33:41.280 --> 00:33:42.630
It's just better to wait.

787
00:33:42.650 --> 00:33:44.510
Then wait.

788
00:33:44.530 --> 00:33:46.050
You know. you can always
work undercover assignments

789
00:33:46.070 --> 00:33:48.010
when on patrol.

790
00:33:48.030 --> 00:33:49.590
So you don't believe I can pass?

791
00:33:49.620 --> 00:33:51.600
I didn't say that. I'm just...

792
00:33:51.620 --> 00:33:53.100
I'm just trying
to be supportive.

793
00:33:53.120 --> 00:33:55.100
By telling me I
can't do something?

794
00:33:55.120 --> 00:33:56.890
You're the one that
said you weren't ready.

795
00:33:56.920 --> 00:33:58.650
N... I-I am in a bad place.

796
00:33:58.670 --> 00:34:00.560
But you just jumped
right in to amplify it.

797
00:34:00.590 --> 00:34:01.900
No. I didn't.

798
00:34:06.390 --> 00:34:07.720
Do you hear me?

799
00:34:09.260 --> 00:34:10.740
What?

800
00:34:10.760 --> 00:34:12.240
That woman in that
car was crying

801
00:34:12.270 --> 00:34:13.950
while she was looking
at the murder scene.

802
00:34:13.980 --> 00:34:15.370
Okay. maybe she knew him.

803
00:34:15.390 --> 00:34:17.160
Or... or maybe she just
had a frustrating fight

804
00:34:17.190 --> 00:34:19.080
with her girlfriend.

805
00:34:42.460 --> 00:34:44.980
Police. Show us your hands.

806
00:34:45.010 --> 00:34:47.780
Uh. I-I'm not doing anything.

807
00:34:47.800 --> 00:34:49.280
- Ma'am. step aside.
- Come over here.

808
00:35:03.530 --> 00:35:05.070
That... that's not mine.

809
00:35:10.700 --> 00:35:12.510
What about this? Megan?

810
00:35:12.530 --> 00:35:14.140
I'm guessing you tossed
the gun. didn't realize

811
00:35:14.160 --> 00:35:15.640
you lost your bracelet
along with it?

812
00:35:20.130 --> 00:35:23.730
I didn't mean to kill him.

813
00:35:23.750 --> 00:35:26.610
He was... he was gonna
tell my husband about us.

814
00:35:26.630 --> 00:35:28.830
All right. ma'am. face that
way. hands behind your back.

815
00:35:35.640 --> 00:35:36.730
Ow.

816
00:35:38.100 --> 00:35:40.710
- Hey. police!
- Show us your hands!

817
00:35:40.730 --> 00:35:42.790
- Hands up!
- Hey. freeze. lady!

818
00:35:42.810 --> 00:35:43.920
Whoa! Whoa!

819
00:35:45.900 --> 00:35:48.170
- Turn around. now!
- Turn around!

820
00:35:57.040 --> 00:35:58.910
Nolan! Watch out!

821
00:36:06.710 --> 00:36:08.270
You okay?

822
00:36:08.300 --> 00:36:10.320
Uh. yeah.

823
00:36:10.340 --> 00:36:11.820
Bet he believes in curses now.

824
00:36:11.840 --> 00:36:12.890
Hmm.

825
00:36:20.940 --> 00:36:22.960
Help me understand
something. Boyd.

826
00:36:22.980 --> 00:36:25.170
You're a Picasso of
big-money heists.

827
00:36:25.190 --> 00:36:26.880
planned to the nth degree.

828
00:36:26.900 --> 00:36:29.380
executed with shocking violence.

829
00:36:29.400 --> 00:36:32.970
But this job was
different. wasn't it?

830
00:36:35.030 --> 00:36:37.930
Can I get a soda?

831
00:36:37.950 --> 00:36:40.430
You didn't just break
into the Federal Reserve

832
00:36:40.460 --> 00:36:42.810
and steal hard currency.

833
00:36:42.830 --> 00:36:44.140
You hacked their computers.

834
00:36:44.170 --> 00:36:46.690
got into servers that
are beyond secret.

835
00:36:46.710 --> 00:36:48.520
Diet. if you have it.

836
00:36:48.550 --> 00:36:51.530
Someone must have
pointed you to them.

837
00:36:51.550 --> 00:36:54.150
an inside man. one that's
a hell of a lot higher up

838
00:36:54.180 --> 00:36:55.970
than that security guard.

839
00:36:58.270 --> 00:37:00.370
You know. I would
settle for a Lacroix.

840
00:37:00.390 --> 00:37:02.080
or any sparkling water. really.

841
00:37:02.100 --> 00:37:04.080
This isn't a joke...
you're gonna spend

842
00:37:04.100 --> 00:37:06.540
the rest of your life
in an 8-foot cell

843
00:37:06.570 --> 00:37:09.210
till they carry you
out in a 6-foot box.

844
00:37:09.230 --> 00:37:10.840
Unless you come clean.

845
00:37:10.860 --> 00:37:12.220
tell us who you
were working with.

846
00:37:17.160 --> 00:37:19.890
Why are you
questioning my client

847
00:37:19.910 --> 00:37:21.850
after he called for his lawyer?

848
00:37:21.870 --> 00:37:24.140
- Nobody was asking questions.
- Well. except for me.

849
00:37:24.170 --> 00:37:25.810
Seriously. can I get that soda?

850
00:37:25.830 --> 00:37:29.210
I'd like to speak to my
client in private... now.

851
00:37:31.420 --> 00:37:32.920
Of course.

852
00:37:34.430 --> 00:37:38.360
While you're at it. I
recommend you emphasize

853
00:37:38.390 --> 00:37:41.580
how tight the vise
is on his nuts.

854
00:37:41.600 --> 00:37:43.190
Ooh.

855
00:37:55.610 --> 00:37:57.880
Hey.

856
00:37:57.910 --> 00:37:59.590
Everything go all right with IA?

857
00:37:59.620 --> 00:38:00.890
Yeah. it was fine.

858
00:38:00.910 --> 00:38:02.810
It should be cleared
in the next day or so.

859
00:38:02.830 --> 00:38:04.390
Good. Well. I'm...

860
00:38:04.410 --> 00:38:06.930
- I'm here if you need me.
- Thanks.

861
00:38:06.960 --> 00:38:09.940
- So you survived.
- Yeah.

862
00:38:09.960 --> 00:38:11.360
My last shift is
officially over.

863
00:38:11.380 --> 00:38:12.670
and I am still standing.

864
00:38:14.880 --> 00:38:18.650
Why? Why do you insist
on tempting fate?

865
00:38:18.680 --> 00:38:19.910
I think because I
know it upsets you.

866
00:38:19.930 --> 00:38:22.430
Huh. You're going to hell.

867
00:38:24.730 --> 00:38:26.080
I tried everything.

868
00:38:26.100 --> 00:38:27.330
but they're knocking
that house down

869
00:38:27.350 --> 00:38:28.710
this weekend during our wedding.

870
00:38:28.730 --> 00:38:29.960
We're gonna have to call it off.

871
00:38:29.980 --> 00:38:31.170
No. no. God. no.

872
00:38:31.190 --> 00:38:33.000
We're not canceling the wedding.

873
00:38:33.030 --> 00:38:34.800
Well. then I'm gonna be
the only bride in history

874
00:38:34.820 --> 00:38:36.630
to wear ear protection
with her wedding dress.

875
00:38:36.660 --> 00:38:38.260
Yeah. that's entirely possible.

876
00:38:38.280 --> 00:38:39.680
I'm so sorry this is happening.

877
00:38:39.700 --> 00:38:41.300
What's happening?

878
00:38:41.330 --> 00:38:44.970
Oh. uh. just our home
wedding is a disaster.

879
00:38:45.000 --> 00:38:47.140
and it's too late
to change the venue.

880
00:38:47.170 --> 00:38:49.190
Oh. I mean. you guys
could get married

881
00:38:49.210 --> 00:38:52.150
at my family's spiritual
oasis downtown.

882
00:38:52.170 --> 00:38:54.980
Your family has a
spiritual oasis downtown?

883
00:38:55.010 --> 00:38:57.440
He asked him with
great admiration.

884
00:38:57.470 --> 00:38:58.780
Oh. yeah. Zen Gardens.

885
00:38:58.800 --> 00:39:01.360
It's a perfect.
stylish party space.

886
00:39:01.390 --> 00:39:03.200
- How many guests?
- Both: 75.

887
00:39:03.220 --> 00:39:04.620
Okay. yeah. no problem.

888
00:39:04.640 --> 00:39:06.790
We can handle. like. five
times as many as that.

889
00:39:06.810 --> 00:39:09.750
- Both: That's...
- So kind of you. Aaron.

890
00:39:09.770 --> 00:39:11.830
- But we couldn't ask you to...
- We couldn't?

891
00:39:11.860 --> 00:39:14.380
Well. you're not
asking. I'm offering.

892
00:39:14.400 --> 00:39:16.380
And it's the least I could
do for you saving my life.

893
00:39:16.400 --> 00:39:17.710
Well. I didn't save your life.

894
00:39:17.740 --> 00:39:19.380
Some very talented
doctors and nurses did.

895
00:39:19.410 --> 00:39:20.720
- Bailey.
- I'm just saying.

896
00:39:20.740 --> 00:39:22.760
Right. but you got me to them.

897
00:39:22.780 --> 00:39:24.800
So y'all are getting
married at the Gardens.

898
00:39:24.830 --> 00:39:26.220
and that's the end of that.

899
00:39:26.250 --> 00:39:27.770
Thank you. Thank you very much.

900
00:39:27.790 --> 00:39:29.310
- No problem.
- Now I really am gonna cry.

901
00:39:29.330 --> 00:39:30.730
Yeah.

902
00:39:30.750 --> 00:39:31.980
- Thank you.
- No problem. Mm-hmm.

903
00:39:32.000 --> 00:39:33.230
Oh. my God. thank you.

904
00:39:33.250 --> 00:39:34.770
Yo. Ishani.

905
00:39:34.800 --> 00:39:37.150
Hey. what's up? This is Aaron.

906
00:39:39.380 --> 00:39:41.570
It's me.

907
00:39:41.600 --> 00:39:44.780
Boyd might be a problem.

908
00:39:44.810 --> 00:39:47.330
Yeah. he's facing
life in prison.

909
00:39:47.350 --> 00:39:49.160
If they offer him
a good-enough deal.

910
00:39:49.190 --> 00:39:50.600
he's likely to take it.

911
00:39:52.560 --> 00:39:55.960
Um. that kind of advice

912
00:39:55.980 --> 00:39:57.650
costs extra.

913
00:40:00.160 --> 00:40:02.130
100 grand.

914
00:40:02.160 --> 00:40:03.970
Good.

915
00:40:03.990 --> 00:40:06.830
Then my advice is simple.

916
00:40:08.910 --> 00:40:11.180
You should do whatever
makes you sleep

917
00:40:11.210 --> 00:40:14.190
the most soundly at night.

918
00:40:14.210 --> 00:40:16.310
No. no. thank you.

919
00:40:19.550 --> 00:40:21.740
Way to pull off the
fourth-quarter win.

920
00:40:21.760 --> 00:40:23.490
Thanks.

921
00:40:23.510 --> 00:40:24.780
What?

922
00:40:24.800 --> 00:40:28.280
Nothing.

923
00:40:28.310 --> 00:40:31.910
This isn't gonna work if
you're gonna lie to me.

924
00:40:31.940 --> 00:40:34.170
Fine.

925
00:40:34.190 --> 00:40:35.920
Did you undermine me today
because you're scared

926
00:40:35.940 --> 00:40:37.380
that I'm gonna make detective?

927
00:40:37.400 --> 00:40:38.710
What? No.

928
00:40:38.740 --> 00:40:41.010
- Tim...
- No.

929
00:40:41.030 --> 00:40:42.550
And I'm upset you'd
even think that.

930
00:40:42.570 --> 00:40:44.590
Look. I don't know. Maybe
it wasn't deliberate.

931
00:40:44.620 --> 00:40:46.390
Maybe it was subconscious.

932
00:40:46.410 --> 00:40:48.140
So... so now
you're accusing me

933
00:40:48.160 --> 00:40:49.430
of being unaware of my actions?

934
00:40:49.450 --> 00:40:51.430
That... that's not better.

935
00:40:51.460 --> 00:40:53.850
You have to admit that
what happened with Isabel

936
00:40:53.880 --> 00:40:55.390
was deeply traumatic for you.

937
00:40:55.420 --> 00:40:57.190
I've never not admitted it.

938
00:40:57.210 --> 00:40:58.810
I admitted it the
first day we met. okay?

939
00:40:58.840 --> 00:41:00.980
So the only thing I did
today was have your back.

940
00:41:01.010 --> 00:41:04.280
But i-if you can't
see that. then...

941
00:41:07.470 --> 00:41:09.700
You know what?

942
00:41:09.720 --> 00:41:11.040
I'm tired.

943
00:41:11.060 --> 00:41:12.330
You've got studying to do.

944
00:41:12.350 --> 00:41:15.040
So let's just take
the night off.

945
00:41:15.060 --> 00:41:17.000
All right? I'll
see you tomorrow.

946
00:41:29.870 --> 00:41:31.830
- Officer Thorsen?
- That's me.

947
00:41:33.420 --> 00:41:34.850
Hi.

948
00:41:34.870 --> 00:41:37.100
I'm Dr. London... uh. Blair.

949
00:41:37.130 --> 00:41:38.850
I'll be working with
you if that's okay.

950
00:41:38.880 --> 00:41:40.360
Yeah.

951
00:41:40.380 --> 00:41:42.070
You seem awesome.

952
00:41:42.090 --> 00:41:44.570
Thanks. but the
jury's still out.

953
00:41:44.590 --> 00:41:46.530
I'm sorry. I
shouldn't be joking.

954
00:41:46.550 --> 00:41:49.820
I graduated last year. and
I've been here six months.

955
00:41:49.850 --> 00:41:51.890
But I promise. I do
know what I'm doing.

956
00:41:53.310 --> 00:41:54.330
Glad one of us does.

957
00:41:54.350 --> 00:41:56.600
This way.
